12. PyTorch Training Steps
outputs = model(inputs)

loss = criterion(outputs, labels)

optimizer.zero_grad()

loss.backward()

optimizer.step()
Explanation

outputs = model(inputs)

Performs the forward pass.

loss = criterion(outputs, labels)

Computes the prediction error.

optimizer.zero_grad()

Clears gradients from the previous iteration.

loss.backward()

Calculates gradients using backpropagation.

optimizer.step()

Updates the model parameters.

